Description: Red granite temple-relief, from a gateway in the temple at Bubastis, showing relief representations of Osorkon II and Karomama, his wife, standing in adoration before an unidentified deity, with cartouches above; some traces of colour survive.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Basta (Bubastis), Temple of Bastet, gateway (?) (?)
Bibliographic references: Monaco 2008 / Queens of Egypt: from Hetepheres to Cleopatra
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 2008 Jul-Sep, Monaco, Grimaldi Forum, Reines de Egyptes
Associated names: Named in inscription & portrayed: Osorkon II
Named in inscription & portrayed: Karomama B
